{"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"checkIsolated","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"()","kind":"text"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Discussion","level":2,"anchor":"discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"During executor comparison, the Swift concurrency runtime attempts to compare"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"current and expected executors in a few ways (including “complex” equality"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"between executors (see ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift\/SerialExecutor\/isSameExclusiveExecutionContext(other:)","isActive":true},{"text":"), and if all","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"those checks fail, this method is invoked on the expected executor.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"This method MUST crash if it is unable to prove that the current execution","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"context belongs to this executor. At this point usual executor comparison would"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"have already failed, though the executor may have some external tracking of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"threads it owns, and may be able to prove isolation nevertheless.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A default implementation is provided that unconditionally crashes the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"program, and prevents calling code from proceeding with potentially"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"not thread-safe execution.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"name":"Warning","style":"warning","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This method must crash and halt program execution if unable"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to prove the isolation of the calling context."}]}],"type":"aside"}],"kind":"content"}],"defaultImplementationsSections":[{"anchor":"SerialExecutor-Implementations","title":"SerialExecutor Implementations","identifiers":["doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift\/SerialExecutor\/checkIsolated()-76lg2"]}],"sections":[],"metadata":{"externalID":"s:Scf13checkIsolatedyyF","title":"checkIsolated()","platforms":[{"introducedAt":"8.0","unavailable":false,"beta":false,"deprecated":false,"name":"iOS"},{"name":"iPadOS","unavailable":false,"deprecated":false,"beta":false,"introducedAt":"8.0"},{"name":"Mac Catalyst","unavailable":false,"deprecated":false,"beta":false,"introducedAt":"13.0"},{"name":"macOS","unavailable":false,"deprecated":false,"beta":false,"introducedAt":"10.10"},{"name":"tvOS","unavailable":false,"deprecated":false,"beta":false,"introducedAt":"9.0"},{"name":"visionOS","unavailable":false,"deprecated":false,"beta":false,"introducedAt":"1.0"},{"name":"watchOS","unavailable":false,"deprecated":false,"beta":false,"introducedAt":"2.0"}],"roleHeading":"Instance Method","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"checkIsolated"},{"kind":"text","text":"()"}],"symbolKind":"method","role":"symbol","modules":[{"relatedModules":[],"name":"Swift"}],"required":true},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift","doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift\/SerialExecutor"]]},"abstract":[{"text":"Last resort “fallback” isolation check, called when the concurrency runtime","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"is comparing executors e.g. during ","type":"text"},{"code":"assumeIsolated()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and is unable to prove","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"serial equivalence between the expected (this object), and the current executor.","type":"text"}],"kind":"symbol","schemaVersion":{"major":0,"patch":0,"minor":3},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift\/SerialExecutor\/checkIsolated()"},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/swift\/serialexecutor\/checkisolated()"]}],"references":{"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift":{"role":"collection","url":"\/documentation\/swift","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift","type":"topic","title":"Swift","images":[{"identifier":"Swift-PageImage-card.png","type":"card"}],"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Build apps using a powerful open language."}]},"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/SerialExecutor/checkIsolated()":{"title":"checkIsolated()","type":"topic","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"checkIsolated","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"()","kind":"text"}],"defaultImplementations":1,"abstract":[{"text":"Last resort “fallback” isolation check, called when the concurrency runtime","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"is comparing executors e.g. during ","type":"text"},{"code":"assumeIsolated()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and is unable to prove","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"serial equivalence between the expected (this object), and the current executor.","type":"text"}],"url":"\/documentation\/swift\/serialexecutor\/checkisolated()","role":"symbol","kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift\/SerialExecutor\/checkIsolated()","required":true},"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/SerialExecutor/checkIsolated()-76lg2":{"role":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"checkIsolated"},{"kind":"text","text":"()"}],"url":"\/documentation\/swift\/serialexecutor\/checkisolated()-76lg2","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift\/SerialExecutor\/checkIsolated(